<text top="390" left="92" width="10" height="9" font="3"><b>1. </b></text>
<text top="390" left="113" width="61" height="9" font="3"><b>Paragraph 21 </b></text>
<text top="408" left="113" width="61" height="9" font="0">The paragraph </text>
<text top="408" left="174" width="50" height="9" font="6"><i>should read </i></text>
<text top="426" left="113" width="15" height="9" font="0">21. </text>
<text top="426" left="142" width="343" height="9" font="0">In its resolution 25/1, the Human Rights Council requested OHCHR to monitor the </text>
<text top="438" left="113" width="371" height="9" font="0">human  rights  situation  in  Sri  Lanka,  to  undertake  a  comprehensive  investigation  into </text>
<text top="450" left="113" width="371" height="9" font="0">alleged serious violations of human rights during the period covered by the Lessons Learnt </text>
<text top="462" left="113" width="371" height="9" font="0">and  Reconciliation  Commission,  and  to  present  a  comprehensive  report  followed  by  a </text>
<text top="474" left="113" width="371" height="9" font="0">discussion  on  the  implementation  of  that  resolution  at  its  twenty-eighth  session.  At  its </text>
<text top="486" left="113" width="371" height="9" font="0">organizational  meeting,  held  on  16  February  2015,  the  Council,  pursuant  to  a </text>
<text top="498" left="113" width="371" height="9" font="0">recommendation  of  the  High  Commissioner,  decided  to  postpone  its  consideration  of  the </text>
<text top="510" left="113" width="371" height="9" font="0">report of OHCHR  until its thirtieth session.  The Council  will have before it a  note by the </text>
<text top="522" left="113" width="207" height="9" font="0">Secretariat reflecting that decision (A/HRC/28/23). </text>
<text top="546" left="57" width="2" height="9" font="3"><b> </b></text>
